The hidden blind spot you are still carrying

You added a Store, but your UI still behaves like “panels trigger side effects directly” and the store is just logging.

If you do not make the grid load driven by ProjectState.view_location + view_payload, you will keep getting these edge bugs:

different queries that produce same row counts

different filters that produce same file sets

“skipping reload” while the user expects a semantic change

Your log is already telling you this happened.

Next improvement that will immediately pay off (Google, Apple, Lightroom pattern)

Add a single concept: GridQuery (a small immutable object) and make everything produce it.

People click, Groups click, Folder click, Date click, Search submit, Duplicates view

All dispatch ViewChanged(location, payload)

One place converts that to a GridQuery

One loader executes it, one cancels previous generations

That is how you avoid “death by many background threads” long-term.
